NAME
    lib::hiderename - Hide modules by renaming them

VERSION
    This document describes version 0.001 of lib::hiderename (from Perl
    distribution lib-hiderename), released on 2020-02-13.

SYNOPSIS
     use lib::hiderename 'Foo::Bar'; # Foo/Bar.pm will be renamed to Foo/Bar_hidden.pm

     eval { require Foo::Bar }; # will fail

     # Foo/Bar_hidden.pm will be renamed back to Foo/Bar.pm

DESCRIPTION
    EXPERIMENTAL.

    lib::hiderename can temporarily hide modules for you, e.g. for testing
    purposes. It uses Module::HideRename to rename module files on the
    filesystem.

HOMEPAGE
    Please visit the project's homepage at
    <https://metacpan.org/release/lib-hiderename>.

